hould be. Items will be much rarer and thats good. Makes an achievement stand out more amongst the crowd. Everyone has to have Testament of Venear? There will be common items and then the rarer unique (on FV) things. It will be a bit still before Dragon Killing is a scheduled occurence and not a fly by the seat of your pants risk. I think that lends the charm to FV and places more value on the RP. One character per server, well then one retires and the next starts a career. Or delevel and start over and roleplay that you were cursed or something. Lots of ways to enjoy Firiona Vie EQ without a race for an assured spawn or clockwork quest.<br><br><br>Minuet of Qeynos<br>&quot;shooting off my mouth...again&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udorinadarkdancer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DorinaDarkdancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/28/01 7:57:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=968.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lets try something different</span><hr size=1> Granted I have not played here on Firiona Vie very long, I have a level 17 Vah Shir Warrior, Nahide. Came over from Test server where I had a 53 necro. Once Luclin came out Test was so unstable that if I wanted to actually play the game I had to choose to go elsewhere. I can't stand the idea of going back to the &quot;regular prod servers&quot; as we Test folk call them, so my hubby and I decided to give FV a whirl.<br><br>The low population, more mature player base and new and different ruleset drew us here. Frankly I hate logging on to Tunare just to hear folks in shout and ooc whining and fighting over spawns, insulting each other or general d00dspeak. <br><br>I find TLC + the fact 